      • startUpdateTimer

        public boolean startUpdateTimer(int interval)
        This function will be used for starting up a timer for requesting information of camera current status and SDcard status. Developer could set up the callback function correspondingly by setDjiCameraSystemStateCallBack and by setDjiCameraSdCardInfoCallBack. Both of these functions will be executed once the sdk receive the data from drone.
        Please note that the interval could not be lower than 100ms.
        Overrides:
        startUpdateTimer in class DJICamera
        Parameters:
        interval - Timer run interval
        Returns:
        boolean true for successfully starting Update timer.
            false for informing failure.
        See Also:
        DJICamera.startUpdateTimer(int), setDjiCameraSystemStateCallBack(DJICameraSystemStateCallBack), setDjiCameraSdcardInfoCallBack(DJICameraSdCardInfoCallBack)
